The paper deals with distributed tracking problems, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of randomization in the algorithms also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The problems being studied are related to data monitoring and analysis, which could also place the paper in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of communication complexity and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
